credit.credit-words: For well we know this weary, soiled earth is yet thine own by right of its new birth, since that great cross upreared on Calvary redeemed it from its fault and shame to thee.
Thine still the changeful beauty of the hills, the purple valleys flecked with silver rills, the ocean glistening 'neath the golden rays; they all are thine, and voiceless speak thy praise.
Almighty Father ofall Things that be
Then grant us, Lord, in all things thee to own, to dwell within the shadow of thy throne, to speak and work, to think, and live, and move, reflecting thine own nature, which is love:
that so, by Christ redeemed from sin and shame, and hallowed by thy Spirit's cleansing flame, ourselves, our work, and all our powers may be a sacrifice acceptable to thee.
